                <h2>Ways you can take care of your cat companion!</h2>
                <ul class="tips-list">
                    <li><strong>Regular Brushing:</strong> Helps reduce hairballs and prevents mats.</li>
                    <li><strong>Provide Fresh Water:</strong> Ensure your cat always has access to clean water.</li>
                    <li><strong>Maintain a Clean Litter Box:</strong> A clean litter box encourages good hygiene.</li>
                    <li><strong>Regular Veterinary Visits:</strong> Check-ups help monitor and maintain your cat's health.</li>
                    <li><strong>Balanced Diet:</strong> Feed nutritious food appropriate for your cat's age and activity.</li>
                    <li><strong>Engage in Play and Exercise:</strong> Keep your cat physically active and mentally stimulated.</li>
                    <li><strong>Monitor Weight:</strong> Prevent obesity-related health issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Dental Care:</strong> Regular teeth checks prevent dental diseases.</li>
                    <li><strong>Provide a Safe Environment:</strong> Keep hazards away and offer safe spaces.</li>
                    <li><strong>Observe Behavior Changes:</strong> Changes in behavior can indicate health issues.</li>
                </ul>
